726460f-a.text:
Cypress Hills Street (formerly Fresh Pond Road; background, house thereon), west side, south of Cooper Ave. (foreground), viewed southward across the Mount Carmel Cemetery at about 67th Place and Cooper Ave.  The house prominently shown was the property of D. Kolyer in 1909.  It is not in existence in 1929.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726460f-a.original_title: Queens: Cypress Hills Street - Cooper Avenue

726461f-a.text:
Cypress Hill St., (extreme left, not seen), west side, south of Cooper Ave. (foreground, not seen), showing Daniel Kolyer farmhouse which stood, according to Eugene L. Armbruster, formerly on the east side of Cypress Hill Street.  However, the 1891 Queens Atlas shows a house, belonging to D. Holyer, to have stood on both sides of the street,
the one on the east side failing to show after 1915.

May 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
